      • FunctionalGroupDefinitions

        public FunctionalGroupDefinitions(java.io.InputStream in)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a new functional group definitions object and reads definitions from the specified input stream. The stream will be closed at the end.
        Parameters:
        in - Input stream to read definitions from. Must not be null.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown, if the input stream cannot be read.

    • Method Detail

      • getWarningConsolidator

      • getReadFunctionalGroupLines

        public int getReadFunctionalGroupLines()
        Returns the number of all lines that have been read from the definition file as functional group definition lines. This includes all malformed lines as well and is basically the total of the results of getFunctionalGroupCount(), getDoublesInFunctionalGroupLines() and getFailuresInFunctionalGroupLines().
        Returns:
        Total number of lines that have been read as functional group definitions.

      • getDoublesInFunctionalGroupLines

        public int getDoublesInFunctionalGroupLines()
        Returns the number of functional groups that had no unique id and were overridden.
        Returns:
        Number of functional groups that had doubles.

      • getFailuresInFunctionalGroupLines

        public int getFailuresInFunctionalGroupLines()
        Returns the number of functional group lines, which could not be read successfully and are not part of this object.
        Returns:
        Number of failed functional groups.

      • getFunctionalGroupCount

        public int getFunctionalGroupCount()
        Returns the number of functional groups that were read successfully and can be used.
        Returns:
        Number of functional groups.

      • getFunctionalGroups

      • getFunctionalGroupNames

        Returns:

      • names

        public java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> names()
        Returns an iterator over all names of defined functional groups. The order is undefined. Call getFunctionalGroups() or getFunctionalGroupNames() to get the functional groups in the order that they were defined in the file they were read from.
        Returns:
        Iterator over functional group names.

      • get

        Retrieves the functional group with the specified name.
        Parameters:
        strName - Name of functional group to retrieve. Can be null.
        Returns:
        Functional group or null, if name does not exist or null was passed in.
